OL,5,Cinjuries
OL,7,FMartin English, defending, said he
OL,8,Faccepted the case would be going to
OL,9,Fthe crown court.
OL,11,FDeclining jurisdiction, District Judge
OL,12,FKate Meek said: "I'm going to allocate
OL,13,Fyour case to the crown court for trial.
OL,15,F"It's actually in the same building
OL,16,Fbut upstairs. Your next hearing will
OL,17,Fbe on October 9 and I'm going to bail
OL,18,Fyou to be at that hearing. You're
OL,19,Fbailed to be there, which means you
OL,20,Fhave a duty to be there.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/4
